  "prompt": "What are some of the best Soft Rock songs of all time?",
  "response": "Soft rock, characterized by its smooth melodies, relaxed rhythms, and often heartfelt lyrics, has produced countless timeless songs. Here\u2019s a list of some of the best soft rock songs of all time, spanning several decades:\n\n### 1970s Classics:\n1. **Fleetwood Mac** - \"Dreams\" (1977)\n2. **The Eagles** - \"Hotel California\" (1976)\n3. **Eric Clapton** - \"Wonderful Tonight\" (1977)\n4. **Steely Dan** - \"Reelin' in the Years\" (1972)\n5. **Bread** - \"Everything I Own\" (1972)\n\n### 1980s Favorites:\n1. **Toto** - \"Africa\" (1982)\n2. **Christopher Cross** - \"Sailing\" (1980)\n3. **Air Supply** - \"Making Love Out of Nothing at All\" (1983)\n4. **Phil Collins** - \"Against All Odds (Take a Look at Me Now)\" (1984)\n5. **REO Speedwagon** - \"Keep On Loving You\" (1980)\n\n### 1990s Hits:\n1. **Extreme** - \"More Than Words\" (1990)\n2. **Mr. Big** - \"To Be with You\" (1991)\n3. **Eric Clapton** - \"Tears in Heaven\" (1992)\n4. **The Rembrandts** - \"I\u2019ll Be There for You\" (1995) *(Theme from Friends)*\n5. **Chicago** - \"You\u2019re the Inspiration\" (1984, but still popular in the '90s)\n\n### 2000s and Beyond:\n1. **Train** - \"Drops of Jupiter (Tell Me)\" (2001)\n2. **Lifehouse** - \"You and Me\" (2005)\n3. **Goo Goo Dolls** - \"Iris\" (1998, but remains a staple)\n4. **John Mayer** - \"Your Body Is a Wonderland\" (2001)\n5. **Coldplay** - \"Yellow\" (2000)\n\n### Timeless Ballads:\n1. **Elton John** - \"Your Song\" (1970)\n2. **Simon & Garfunkel** - \"Bridge Over Troubled Water\" (1970)\n3. **America** - \"A Horse with No Name\" (1972)\n4. **The Doobie Brothers** - \"What a Fool Believes\" (1979)\n5. **Chicago** - \"Hard Habit to Break\" (1984)\n\nThese songs have left a lasting impact on the genre and continue to resonate with listeners across generations. Whether you\u2019re looking for nostalgia or discovering soft rock for the first time, these tracks are a great place to start.",
